---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../styles/home.css';
---
<Layout title="Home">

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════
       HERO
  ════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-text animate-fade-in-up">
      <p class="eyebrow">Colombian language educator & researcher</p>
      <h1>
        Spanish is not a code<br/>
        to <em>decode</em> —<br/>
        it is a world<br/>
        to <em>inhabit</em>.
      </h1>
      <p class="subhead">
        Language is an opening — a way of letting other people into your experience. I build environments where Spanish emerges from story, sensation, and meaning, the same way it emerges in life: because someone has something to say and needs the words to say it.
      </p>
      <nav class="hero-nav">
        <a href="/philosophy" class="nav-link">
          <span class="nav-line"></span>
          neuroSpanish methodology
        </a>
        <a href="/geography" class="nav-link secondary">
          <span class="nav-line"></span>
          Field notes & research
        </a>
      </nav>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-figure animate-fade-in-up" aria-hidden="true" style="animation-delay: 0.2s;">
      <div class="orbit-wrap">
        <div class="orbit orbit-1"></div>
        <div class="orbit orbit-2"></div>
        <div class="orbit orbit-3"></div>
        <div class="glyph-core">
          <span>ñ</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- Floating coordinates -->
      <div class="coord coord-bogota">Bogotá, CO</div>
      <div class="coord coord-sevilla">Sevilla, ES</div>
      <div class="coord coord-tarsus">Tarsus, TR</div>
      <div class="coord coord-danang">Đà Nẵng, VN</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="divider">
    <span class="divider-rule"></span>
    <span class="divider-mark">§</span>
    <span class="divider-rule"></span>
  </div>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════
       ABOUT
  ════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="about">
    <div class="about-label">
      <span>Who I am</span>
    </div>
    <div class="about-body">
      <p class="about-lead">
        I grew up in Bogotá with a sense of community that wasn't an abstract value, but something deeply felt. I carry the conviction that belonging to something is not optional for a human being. It shapes how I enter a school, a city, or a classroom.
      </p>
      <p>
        I've lived and taught across four continents — the Andes, the Mediterranean coast of Spain, the orange groves of Turkey, and now Đà Nẵng, Vietnam. My time outside the classroom is spent cycling in the early mornings before the heat, or practicing amateur photography as a way to force myself to actually see what is in front of me.
      </p>
      <p>
        I believe the most important things happen <strong>between people</strong>, not in content or curriculum. Because of this, my practice is oriented by purpose: activities that feel meaningful get my full attention.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="divider">
    <span class="divider-rule"></span>
    <span class="divider-mark">§</span>
    <span class="divider-rule"></span>
  </div>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════
       THREE PILLARS
  ════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="pillars">
    <h2 class="pillars-title">Three pillars of my practice</h2>
    <div class="pillars-grid">
      <article class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-num">01</div>
        <h3>Story before syntax</h3>
        <p>
          Grammar should emerge from narrative. I immerse students in rich, contextualized Spanish from day one — without translation or isolated exercises. Story provides the emotional architecture that makes acquisition stick.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-num">02</div>
        <h3>Body and environment</h3>
        <p>
          Following 4E Cognition, language is not stored in the brain alone. I design lessons that activate the body and the senses, turning acquisition into a lived event.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-num">03</div>
        <h3>Connection first</h3>
        <p>
          Meaningful interaction is the compass. Activities that feel meaningful get full attention; the destination is rarely the point. Genuine curiosity about people forms the core of my teaching.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="divider">
    <span class="divider-rule"></span>
    <span class="divider-mark">§</span>
    <span class="divider-rule"></span>
  </div>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════
       TRAJECTORY
  ════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="trajectory">
    <h2 class="trajectory-title">A practitioner shaped by distance</h2>
    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <span class="tl-place">Colombia</span>
          <span class="tl-detail">Raised in Bogotá. Degree in Education (Humanities and Foreign Languages) · Early pedagogical roots grounded in community</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <span class="tl-place">Turkey</span>
          <span class="tl-detail">Tarsus American College · Cycled the inland orange groves · Designed interactive curricula for over 120 students</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <span class="tl-place">Spain</span>
          <span class="tl-detail">University of Seville · Mapped <em>The Hero's Journey</em> through 4E Cognition for my Master's thesis</em></span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tl-item">
        <div class="tl-dot"></div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <span class="tl-place">Thailand</span>
          <span class="tl-detail">UWC Thailand · Experiential learning and outdoor education with the MANTAS project</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="tl-item tl-item--now">
        <div class="tl-dot tl-dot--now"></div>
        <div class="tl-content">
          <span class="tl-place">Vietnam <span class="now-badge">now</span></span>
          <span class="tl-detail">Living by the coast in Đà Nẵng · Conducting independent research on applied psycholinguistics and developing neuroSpanish</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="divider">
    <span class="divider-rule"></span>
    <span class="divider-mark">§</span>
    <span class="divider-rule"></span>
  </div>

  <!-- ════════════════════════════════════════
       CTA
  ════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <section class="cta">
    <p class="cta-intro">Want to see the full scope of my work, or discuss language and community?</p>
    <div class="cta-links">
      <a href="/cv" class="cta-btn">View full CV</a>
      <a href="/philosophy" class="cta-btn cta-btn--ghost">Read my philosophy</a>
      <a href="mailto:uguinard@gmail.com" class="cta-btn cta-btn--ghost">Get in touch</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
